      • setTime

        public void setTime(java.lang.String time)
        Sets the time for the request. Format should be passed as follows:
        [YYYY]-[MM]-[DD]T[HH]:[MM]:[SS]{+,-}[HH][MM]
        The last {+,-}[HH][MM] is the timezone
        Example:
        [2013-05-06T12:00:00-0400]
        For more information refer to the API Docs: https://developer.forecast.io
        Parameters:
        time - in the described format

      • setUnits

        public void setUnits(java.lang.String units)
        Sets the units to be passed in the request. If the units are unavailable, auto is set.
        Units can be set with constants like ForecastIO.UNITS_AUTO. For more information refer to the API Docs: https://developer.forecast.io
        Parameters:
        units - the units to be set. Units can set with a constant like ForecastIO.UNITS_SI. (If the units are invalid the API will return an error)

      • getLang

        Returns:

      • setLang

        public void setLang(java.lang.String lang)
        Sets the language to be passed in the request. If the language is not unavailable, english is set.
        Units can be set with constants like ForecastIO.LANG_ENGLISH. For more information refer to the API Docs: https://developer.forecast.io
        Parameters:
        lang - the language to set. this can be set with the constant ForecastIO.LANG_ENGLISH (example for english). If a constant is not available for a given an available API language it can be set with the language code. (If the language is invalid the API will return an error)
